This paper deals with a rating system that involves social networks and game theory, which are topics commonly found in the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also discusses the effect of bribery on the system, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CY (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper analyzes the influence of the social network on the rating system, which is related to the sub-categories of cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
